==English==
===Pronunciation===
*lŏ<small>KH</small>, /lɒx/, /lQx/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɒx|Rhymes: -ɒx]]
*(often mispronounced) lŏk, /lɒk/, /lQk/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɒk|Rhymes: -ɒk]]

===Etymology 1===
Gaelic ''loch''. See [[lake]] (of water).

====Noun====
'''loch''' (''plural'' '''lochs''')

# {{Scotland}} A lake; a bay or arm of the sea.

=====Translations=====
*Finnish: [[järvi]]

===Etymology 2===
French ''[[looch]]'', Arabic ''[[la'g]]'', an [[electuary]], or any medicine which may be licked or sucked, from ''la'g''' to lick

====Noun====
'''loch''' (''plural'' '''lochs''') (''or is this uncountable?'')
#(''medicine'') A kind of medicine to be taken by licking with the tongue; a [[lambative]]; a [[lincture]].

